\end{figure}

The second source, HAIEnd+, exposes the internal function block outputs of the 
distributed control system (DCS)---signals such as \texttt{1001.x-OUT}, 
\texttt{DM-PP04-D}, and \texttt{DM-FT03Z}---that remain invisible in standard process 
historian logs, revealing the DCS layer's decision-making process before commands reach 
physical actuators. The control logic underlying these signals, exemplified by the 
pressure control algorithm blocks of the Emerson Ovation DCS, is shown in Figure~\ref{fig: HAIEnd 23.05}

