\subsubsection{\textbf{Data Preprocessing}}
 The raw HAI~23.05 and HAIEnd~23.05 dataset comprises six CSV 
files that are aligned chronologically and partitioned into training, validation, 
and test sets following a strict temporal ordering to prevent data leakage. The entire dataset has over 80 sensors and around 1.5 million rows on all the files. All data is processed per second at 1Hz frequency to track every change in the plant's behavior, and capture anomalies more precisely.  In addition, the exact same data pipeline was used in both the primary and baseline models to guaranty fair comparisons. 
\texttt{train1} and \texttt{train2} are used entirely for training; \texttt{train3} is 
split temporally, with the first 30\% contributing to training and the remaining 70\% 
reserved exclusively for validation; \texttt{train4} is held out completely as the test 
set for evaluating cross-period generalisation and was never seen during training or used 
for scaler fitting. Attack segments from \texttt{test1} and \texttt{test2} are extracted 
with a 300\,s pre-attack context window and a 180\,s post-attack window, then split 
80/20 into training and test sets using stratified sampling by attack type, yielding the 
distribution shown in Table~\ref{tab:attack_split}.


