\subsubsection{\textbf{Loss Functions}}

To bridge the training/inference gap introduced by teacher forcing, scheduled
sampling~\cite{bengio2015scheduled} is applied to the plant decoder. The mixing
ratio $\alpha$ ramps linearly from 0 to a maximum of $0.483$ over the scheduled
epochs; at each decoding step, with probability $\alpha$ the model's own
previous prediction is used as the next input instead of the ground truth:
%
\begin{equation}
  \tilde{\mathbf{y}}_{t-1} =
  \begin{cases}
    \hat{\mathbf{y}}_{t-1} & \text{with probability } \alpha \\
    \mathbf{y}_{t-1}       & \text{with probability } 1 - \alpha
  \end{cases}
\end{equation}

\paragraph{Stage~1 Loss.}
A uniform attack penalty is applied: all attack windows (scenario $> 0$) are
weighted $3\times$ relative to normal windows. The temperature sensor
\texttt{P1\_TIT03} receives an additional $2\times$ channel weight, yielding an
effective $6\times$ penalty on its attack-window errors. The weighted loss for
a batch of $B$ windows is:
%
\begin{equation}
  \mathcal{L}_{\text{plant}} =
  \frac{1}{B}\sum_{b=1}^{B} w_b
  \!\left[
    \frac{1}{T}\sum_{t=1}^{T}
    \left(
      \bigl\|\hat{\mathbf{y}}_{b,t}^{[{:}4]} - \mathbf{y}_{b,t}^{[{:}4]}\bigr\|^2
      + 2\,\bigl\|\hat{y}_{b,t}^{[4]} - y_{b,t}^{[4]}\bigr\|^2
    \right)
  \right]
  \label{eq:stage1_loss}
\end{equation}
%
where $w_b = 3$ if window $b$ contains an attack, and $w_b = 1$ otherwise.

\paragraph{Stage~2 Loss.}
The uniform attack penalty of Stage~1 is replaced with \emph{per-scenario}
loss weights calibrated to the data imbalance and reconstruction difficulty
of each attack type:
%
\begin{equation}
  \mathcal{L}_{\text{plant}} =
  \frac{1}{B}\sum_{b=1}^{B} w_{s_b}
  \!\left[
    \frac{1}{T}\sum_{t=1}^{T}
    \left(
      \bigl\|\hat{\mathbf{y}}_{b,t}^{[{:}4]} - \mathbf{y}_{b,t}^{[{:}4]}\bigr\|^2
      + 2\,\bigl\|\hat{y}_{b,t}^{[4]} - y_{b,t}^{[4]}\bigr\|^2
    \right)
  \right]
  \label{eq:stage2_loss}
\end{equation}
%
where $w_{s_b}$ is the scenario weight for window $b$, defined in
Table~\ref{tab:scenario_weights}.

